author: Andrew Tornetta
title: Heritage-Delray pounds Fort Pierce Central
text:
Coming off a shocking home loss last week to Oxbridge, American Heritage-Delray rebounded in a big way against visiting Fort Pierce Central, beating the Cobras 43-7 in a non-district on Friday night.
The Stallions pounced early, jumping ahead 16-0 after the first quartera nd led 30-7 at halftime.
Devin Singletary took over early, running the ball 10 times in the first quarter for 48 yards and two touchdowns. The senior running back finished the game with 125 yards on 22 carries and three scores. Senior Cornelius Smith complemented Singletary nicely with a big game of his own, carrying the rock 20 times for 159 yards and two touchdowns.
While the Stallions (4-2) offense was putting up points in bunches, the defense stymied a very good Cobras offense that was averaging 32 points per game entering the night.`
The American Heritage defense held Fort Pierce (4-2) to just 181 total yards, forced three fumbles, and picked off a pair of passes, both of which came at the hands of senior linebacker Logan Wakefield.
